HOUSTON - Johnny Nash, the 1970’s I Can See Clearly Now hitmaker, has died. The American reggae and pop music singer-songwriter passed away at the age of 80. Nash died from natural causes at his home in Houston. Having started his career as a pop singer in the 1950's, he signed greats such as Bob Marley and other members of the group, The Wailers. Nash was one of the first non-Jamaican singers to record reggae music in Kingston, Jamaica.